There are seveal stuff that need to be installed but I will make it easy. 

Some comments:

1. This is for Ubuntu 16.04, but will work on other Linux distros without problems, as far as I understand. 
2. We need to install a local ethereum (ganache-cli), the solidity framework deployment (truffle) and a google chrome extension (metamask) to manage accounts and ETH.


This doc is only for installation and some brief comments. In the end, you will have installed all necessary stuff to start playing.

Sublime editor: (highlights syntax solidity)

wget -qO - https://download.sublimetext.com/sublimehq-pub.gpg | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb https://download.sublimetext.com/ apt/stable/" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/sublime-text.list
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install sublime-text
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Install node and npm, to play and interact with local ethereum

wget -qO- https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_8.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
sudo apt-get install nodejs-legacy
sudo apt-get install npm

------------------------------------------------------------

Now we install ganache-cli and truffle

npm install -g ganache-cli
sudo npm install -g express
sudo npm install -g truffle 

-------------------------------------------------------------

Install metamask extension on chrome. Log in to get a default account. 



That's it 
